Selecting the top 3 classes with highest image count¶

In [12]:
class_counts = {}

for class_folder in class_folders:
    class_name = os.path.basename(class_folder)
    image_count = len(list(class_folder.glob("*.jpg")))
    class_counts[class_name] = image_count

sorted_classes = sorted(class_counts.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)

top_three_classes = sorted_classes[:3]

for class_name, image_count in top_three_classes:
    print(f"Top Class: {class_name}, Image Count: {image_count}")

Top Class: RUFOUS TREPE, Image Count: 263
Top Class: HOUSE FINCH, Image Count: 248
Top Class: D-ARNAUDS BARBET, Image Count: 233

Image Data Generator Configuration for Training Augmentation¶

In [13]:
train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1./255,
    rotation_range=40,
    width_shift_range=0.2,
    height_shift_range=0.2,
    shear_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    fill_mode='nearest'
)

Training Data Generator Initialization¶

In [14]:
train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    data_dir.joinpath(split),
    target_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='categorical',
    classes=[cls_name for cls_name, _ in top_three_classes]
)

Found 744 images belonging to 3 classes.

Display Augmented Images¶

In [17]:
def display_augmented_images(batch_images, batch_labels):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 15))

    for img_index, (image, label) in enumerate(zip(batch_images, batch_labels)):
        if img_index >= 25:
            break

        plt.subplot(5, 5, img_index + 1)
        plt.imshow(image)
        plt.title(label)
        plt.axis("off")

    plt.show()

augmented_images, augmented_labels = next(train_generator)
class_labels = [class_name for class_name, _ in top_three_classes]
augmented_class_names = [class_labels[np.argmax(label)] for label in augmented_labels]

display_augmented_images(augmented_images, augmented_class_names)

Using VGG16 for Image Classification¶

In [16]:
base_model = VGG16(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(224, 224, 3))
for layer in base_model.layers:
    layer.trainable = False

model = models.Sequential()
model.add(base_model)
model.add(layers.Flatten())
model.add(layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'))
model.add(layers.Dense(len(top_three_classes), activation='softmax'))
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
history = model.fit(train_generator, epochs=10, validation_data=train_generator)
